<section id="faq" class="faq section-padding">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details>
        <summary class="faq-item">
          <span>What is Gemini Advanced?</span>
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
        </summary>
          <div class="faq-content"><p>Gemini Advanced is a premium version of the Gemini AI model, offering enhanced capabilities and features.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary class="faq-item">
           <span>How do I upgrade to Gemini Advanced?</span>
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
        </summary>
           <div class="faq-content"><p>To upgrade to Gemini Advanced, navigate to the upgrade section on the product platform or within your account settings.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary class="faq-item">
          <span>Will Gemini Advanced work in the Gemini mobile app?</span>
           <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
        </summary>
           <div class="faq-content"><p>Yes, Gemini Advanced is designed to function seamlessly within the Gemini mobile app, providing access to its advanced features.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary class="faq-item">
          <span>How do I know which model Gemini is using in its responses?</span>
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
        </summary>
           <div class="faq-content"><p>The model being used is often indicated in the response information or within the app settings. Look for a model indicator within the response itself.</p></div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq {
    text-align: left;
  }

  .faq h2 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    text-align: center;
    color: rgb(var(--color-text));
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .faq-list {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .faq-list details {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(var(--color-primary), 0.2);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: rgba(var(--color-primary), 0.05);
  }

  .faq-list details[open] {
    background: rgba(var(--color-primary), 0.1);
  }

   .faq-item {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      cursor: pointer;
      list-style: none;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
     padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
   }

  .faq-list summary {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
    .faq-list summary::-webkit-details-marker {
        display: none;
    }


 .faq-list details:not([open]) .faq-content {
      overflow: hidden;
      max-height: 0;
 }
    .faq-list .faq-content {
        transition: max-height 0.3s ease-in-out;
    }
  .faq-list p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgb(var(--color-text-light));
      padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

    .faq-item svg {
       transition: transform 0.3s ease-in-out;
    }
   .faq-list details[open] summary svg {
      transform: rotate(180deg);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .faq h2 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }

        .faq-list summary {
            font-size: 1rem;
        }
    }
</style>